I met Captain a few months back @northcentralshelter where he’s been stuck for almost two years.💔💔💔As everyone knows our boxes are meant to help network animals who need forever homes in a fun way. Anyone who reposts and shares Captains story by tagging us and hashtags #oneheartadopt will be eligible to win our March box.
💘
💘
Once upon a time a dog named Captain found himself at a scary shelter. He wished upon all the stars that one day someone would come and whisk him to safety. Sadly, day after day, week after week, a year and now almost two no one came. But he still wishes for magic with all his might that one day his dream will come true. Captain is a lovable teddy bear who's ready to curl up by the fire place, snuggle and drink hot coco. He's waiting for his fairytale ending full of magic and treats.
Captain has been friendly with dogs (med/large), both male and female, he has met at the shelter on walks and dropped leash play dates. He might like to live with a canine companion in his new home (slow intros always recommended 😊)!
💘
Interested in adopting Captain?

My composite of one image of each animal that I photographed for Houston area Rescues in 2017. 267 on here but I seem to be missing a few, I had counted 275 so I am not sure who I left off...I had to take some time off right after Hurricane Harvey flooded us at the end of August and in all that mess I seem to have lost my chart of past years' totals but 2017 has to be less than when I shot weekly at Animal Control. I mostly shoot for 4 Rescues though will photograph if I can for others when asked. These animals were all saved. I am one volunteer photographer in one city, I know of several more around Houston, all trying to help the thousands and thousands of homeless pets just in our area. In the 8 years I have been doing this I do not think anything has changed as far as the number of abandoned animals. I love Best Friends' motto ---- Save Them All...we are still trying.

Jake #A5129878 is also a new transfer to Castaic. Jake is a 2 year old chihuahua who is a little ball of energy! He loves to run around and play. When he is in his kennel he will jump like a little kangaroo to try and get your attention. Jake loves people and seems to get along with other dogs. Jake would likely do well with another dog that has his matched energy level. Jake needs a little leash and obedience training but he is a smart guy and will catch on quick. Come and meet him today at the Castaic Shelter. 31044 N. Charlie Canyon Rd. Castaic , CA. 91384. Hours: Mon-Thurs 12-7 and Fri-Sun 10-5. Jake #A5129878 is also a new transfer to Castaic. Jake is a 2 year old chihuahua who is a little ball of energy! He loves to run around and play. When he is in his kennel he will jump like a little kangaroo to try and get your attention. Jake loves people and seems to get along with other dogs. Jake would likely do well with another dog that has his matched energy level. Jake needs a little leash and obedience training but he is a smart guy and will catch on quick. Come and meet him today at the Castaic Shelter. 31044 N. Charlie Canyon Rd. Castaic , CA. 91384. Hours: Mon-Thurs 12-7 and Fri-Sun 10-5. Sasha Obama is a two-year-old, 50lb Lab mix. She’s a smart girl who’s already housebroken and knows sit, down, wait, and leave it — so you can move onto more advanced tricks, like roll over, do a cartwheel, and write the next great American novel. This sweetheart loves being outside, and will gladly play ball or chase with you as long as you’ll let her. On colder days, she has an absolute blast frolicking in the snow. Now that she’s moved out of the White House, she’s looking for a new place to call home. Can she move in with you? Sasha is spayed, microchipped, and up to date on vaccines. Email seespotrescued@gmail.com for an adoption application. #SSRSashaObama
